Filenames
=========

Modern desktop environments have obsoleted the need for filename extensions.


- No limitation on filename length
- Spaces and many other special characters permissible
- No longer a need for filename extensions

For instance, the "exe" extension is no longer necessary because the OS knows whether a file in executable. The executability of a file is visually indicated to the user in file browsers and terminal emulators.

What is a File Name?
--------------------

The ultimate purpose of a filename is *organization*.

### Extensions

Filename extensions can still be useful for filing purposes. They no longer necessarily have a special meaning, and can

- No longer necessarily have a machine-readable meaning
- No longer have a length limitation and can be stacked
- Good human-readable visual indicator of a file's purpose

